page.title: 19WILDLIFE AT GOLLANFIELD
page.content: { SWAN} The swans around our area are called mute swans.They have orange-yellow beaks and hardly ever make a noise . A {cygnet }stays with its mother for around two years and then it goes off. Not many swans survive for they quite often fly into the electricity wires. {COOT { }The coots are very fearful animals and they hate anything going near their nests but they have a good way of chasing them away. {HERON { }The Heron is a tall dark-grey bird which eats a lot of frogs, but it is a very patient bird for it waits for its prey to come to it.
